    <h1 class="big-heading">Co-occurring Disorders</h1>

    <p>

        Substance abuse, including the use of alcohol and drugs, may increase the likelihood of developing mental health
        problems. While the underlying causes of mental health issues are frequently complex and multifaceted, substance
        abuse can exacerbate already existing risks. Heavy opioid use, for example, has been linked to an increased risk
        of depression, and cannabis abuse has been linked to an increased risk of schizophrenia.

    </p>

    <div class="center">
