    <h2 class="section-heading">Treatment</h2>

    <p>

        To effectively manage symptoms and achieve long-term recovery, co-occurring disorder treatment typically
        consists of a combination of medications and behavioral therapies. Co-occurring disorders, if left untreated,
        can have serious consequences such as an increased risk of overdose, hospitalization, and premature death.

        <br><br>

        Individuals suffering from co-occurring disorders should seek specialized treatment programs that can address
        both conditions concurrently while also providing the necessary support and resources for recovery.

    </p>

